When I make ribs I usually do them low and slow in the oven, 275 F. for four hours or so. This also makes it so that I can just give the protruding end of the bones a little twist and they come right out. You know how each rib bone has a narrow flattened end and a broad flared end that's a little thicker? The thicker ends seem to break down a bit from the heat and are mostly marrow, and are edible. Sometimes i get that craving. Bone marrow has iron and vitamins, I guess, and some Internet "nutrition experts" seem to be trying to make it the next big food fad. The texture is a bit crumbly and gritty.

To be entirely fair, they keep changing the definitions and making them more expansive. Fifty years ago, if you looked in the DSM-3, "autism" was a label reserved solely for a particular category of profoundly mentally retarded children who never learned to speak and did not even appear to be trying to communicate, the ones who exhibited certain particular categories of repetitive behaviors. Since around 2000, though, does a kid learn to read earlier than the others in his class? AUTISM! Does he have difficulty learning to read and take longer than others? AUTISM! Is he shy? AUTISM! Is he outgoing and talkative? AUTISM! The word has become a meaningless noise that's used as a playground insult, not just in pop-culture but in the scientific literature. I sometimes think we should throw away the "soft sciences" and start over.

My writing, and a few other people's writing, even if the content was good, the characters were good, and the plot was good, could sometimes feel empty and poorly flowing. For the longest time, I could never figure out what was wrong with it. Sentence structure is to blame.
Observe:

>Tom knew he wanted milk, so he went to the store. The store always had high quality milk. The store even had cute girls there. Tom knew the girls there were single, so he planned to spend some extra time shopping.
Vs
>Thirsty for milk, Tom went to the store. Milk from this store was always high quality. Hell, there were even some cute girls there who were single. Maybe he would spend some extra time 'shopping around'...

The same information is conveyed, but just tweaking the arrangement of words makes one far more communicative.
